This paper is primarily focused on cooperative game theory, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also discusses stability and social welfare, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The computational perspective mentioned in the abstract suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
